CANOPY_CATTOOHIGHWARNING: You lack the experience to fly this canopy. Its categorized higher then you at this point in your jumping career.
CANOPY_NOTCATEGORIZEDYET: Not categorized yet. Until then the category is:
CANOPY_SIZEWARNING: You can fly this type of canopy, as long as the wingload doesn't get too high. Take your minimum size into account
CANOPY_WINGLOADWARNING: This results in the wingload being too high, so in spite of the category you're not allowed to jump this parachute.
EXPERIENCE_INTRO: Set your skydiving experience and see what parachutes are acceptable according to Dutch regulations.
EXPERIENCE_NEEDED_2: At least 25 jumps, of which at least 10 in the last 12 months
EXPERIENCE_NEEDED_3: At least 100 jumps, of which at least 25 in the last 12 months
EXPERIENCE_NEEDED_4: At least 400 jumps, of which at least 50 in the last 12 months
EXPERIENCE_NEEDED_5: At least 700 jumps, of which at least 100 in the last 12 months
EXPERIENCE_NEEDED_7: At least 1200 jumps, of which 200 with a cat VI cross-braced canopy
JUMPERCATEGORIES_1: Less then 25 jumps, or less then 10 jumps in the last 12 months
JUMPERCATEGORIES_2: 25 to 100 jumps; at least 10 jumps in the last 12 months
JUMPERCATEGORIES_3: 100 to 400 jumps; at least 25 jumps in the last 12 months
JUMPERCATEGORIES_4: 400 to 700 jumps; at least 50 jumps in the last 12 months
JUMPERCATEGORIES_5: 700 to 1000 jumps; at least 75 jumps in the last 12 months
JUMPERCATEGORIES_6: 1000 jumps or more, at least 100 jumps in the last 12 months
JUMPERCATEGORIES_7: 1200 jumps or more; at least 200 with a cat VI cross-braced canopy including at least 100 in the last 12 months
SLIDER_JUMPSLAST12MONTHS_L: Number of jumps in the last 12 months
SLIDER_JUMPSXBRACED_L: Total number of jumps on cross based canopies
WEIGHT_INTRO: Set your exit weight and see what parachutes are allowed according to Dutch parachuting federation regulations.
